  "name": "Acts 9:20–31",
  "localizedName": "Acts 9:20–31",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Saul’s life completely changed after he saw Jesus on the road to Damascus. He became fully committed to telling everyone about Jesus."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "He preached in "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108051",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "synagogues"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". He used the Scriptures to show Jews that Jesus is the Messiah. People were shocked at the change in Saul. Some Jews in Damascus made plans to kill him. The suffering that Jesus had talked about started for Saul."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Saul escaped to Jerusalem but the believers there were afraid of him. "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108107",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Barnabas"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " helped the believers to trust Saul and the work Jesus had done in his life. When Saul’s life was once again in danger he had to leave Jerusalem."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Meanwhile, the church kept growing. There were believers in Jerusalem and Judea as well as north in "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108036",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Galilee"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and Samaria."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
